IBADAN – As part of his efforts to ad­dress the disunity among the people of Oke Ogun geo-political zone of Oyo State and also to attract development to the area, a member of House of Repre­sentatives representing Is­eyin/ Itesiwaju/ Iwajowa/ Kajola federal constituency, Hon. Shina Abiola Peller has unveiled Peller Unity Cup (PUC) Session II. He maintained that only sports can bring the needed unity and develop­ment to the zone. Peller made the disclo­sure while speaking at a press conference herald­ing the second edition of the Peller Unity Cup (PUC) at Okeho in Kajola local government area of the state. Orientation: Call-Up-Letters Out On Sunday, COVID-19 Rapid… Ikeja Golden Lions Club Applauded For Touching Lives Of… Oke Ogun, which falls under Oyo North Sena­torial District, consists of 10 local government areas. Speaking at the event which had the attendance of Onjo of Okeho, Oba Rafiu Osuolale, represen­tative of Aseyin of Iseyin, Oba Abdulganiy Adekunle Ologunebi, ex-internation­al players, Dosu Joseph and Femi Opabunmi among others, Peller expressed displeasure over low de­velopment in Oke Ogun as a region in Oyo State. He said that the major contributing factor to the stagnant stage of the re­gion is disunity. Peller, however, insist­ed that the only panacea to bring unity and devel­opment to the region is sports. The federal lawmaker noted that football, being a universal language that everyone understands, will help connect people of the region, stressing that he introduced the competition in order to address the disunity among people of the area. POLL While addressing the au­dience, Peller remarked that sports especially football will be an avenue to help bring the people together as one, and that will at the same time promote peace, youth engagement and de­velop­ment.